parameters:
\nc<>What's going on here? Are these people wrapped in slime?
Could they have been kidnapped?

\nc<>...No, that's not it! These people weren't kidnapped. This
is...!

\nc<>This... the monsters have transformed into humans,
meow...!
\nc<>Is it possible to do such a thing!?

\nc<>I... I don't understand, meow. This is the first time I've
seen a case like this, meow...

\nc<>(For now, it seems like it would be good to destroy the
machine-like thing inside...)

\nc<>Phew. What are you hesitating for? We can't just leave this
alone! Let's go, Cashew Nut!

\nc<>Eek... This isn't a machine, it's a monster, meow. What on
earth has happened to this creature, meow...

\nc<>...! Cashew Nut, come here for a moment. Can you read
this?

\nc<>Hmmm? Is this the language of another world, meow? Let's
try casting a translation spell for now, meow.
\nc<>I see, I kind of understand now, meow.

\nc<>This %^@&!... when translated, it seems to be called
Invasoid, meow.

\nc<>It's not a precise translation, but it seems like it was
researched in relation to weapons and then disposed of
across dimensions, meow.

\nc<>Mimicking humans is also a function to destroy communities,
meow.

\nc<>The sure thing is that nothing good will happen if we leave
it alone.

\nc<>It would be better to go back for now. It seems that the
Invasoid has taken root deeper in this entire sewer than I
thought.

\nc<>Okay, understood. But let's take as much time as we can and
exterminate the Invasoid in the sewer from now on.
\nc<>I obtained the memory T2: Invasoid of Another World.

\nc<>Good listeners increased by 7,000 people, and bad listeners
increased by 3,000 people.
